{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"22c88c71-01b5-401e-aeb7-9662320835d5","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed first.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_y0j6pCgpbKQgFdeHPjzVd5","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-fdb08dc90f554f5caf9452ce57bc153c/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-fdb08dc90f554f5caf9452ce57bc153c/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"33414de0-8943-4fa1-a44e-c6c953347407","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, which means it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` comes after `Services.fs` in the compile order, the build will fail.\n\nThe fix is to reorder the files so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nThis way, `Services.fs` can properly reference the types and modules defined in `Domain.fs`.","outputTokens":468,"requestId":"2826:5FB6B:1BFE22A:1F0B9F9:69FA8FDE"},"id":"444e65d6-6445-4c53-b835-aedb14991770","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:38.054Z","parentId":"1a60cef5-81f2-493b-bcd0-e4a1ed109911"}
